    <p>Welcome to Visionet's Selenium Automation Testing Framework. This powerful framework integrates Cucumber, BDD, and TestNG to deliver efficient and effective testing for web applications. Explore the features and setup below to get started.</p>

   <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        The Visionet Automation Suite Framework leverages the capabilities of Selenium WebDriver for browser automation, coupled with Cucumber for BDD and TestNG as the testing engine. This combination ensures a robust and maintainable strategy for web application testing.
    </p>

## About Framework
 
<p>The Visionet Automation Suite Framework is crafted to streamline web application testing. Utilizing Selenium WebDriver for automation, Cucumber for BDD, and TestNG as the testing engine, this framework supports scalable and maintainable testing strategies. Whether you're testing complex web applications or simple websites, this suite provides the tools you need to ensure quality and performance.</p>

   <h2>Key Features</h2>

   <h3>1. BDD Approach</h3>
    <p>
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/Java/17/007396?icon=java" alt="Java 17 Badge"> &nbsp;
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/Selenium/4.0/43B02A?icon=selenium" alt="Selenium 4.0 Badge"> &nbsp;<br>
        Uses pure advanced Java 17 and the latest Selenium version 4.0. Employs Cucumber for Behavior Driven Development (BDD) to create easily understandable and maintainable test scripts.
    </p>

   <h3>2. Testing Engine</h3>
    <p>
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/TestNG/7.4.0/1F4E78?icon=testng" alt="TestNG 7.4.0 Badge"> &nbsp;
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/Extent%20Reports/2.0/006400" alt="Extent Reports 2.0 Badge"> &nbsp;
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/Log4j/2/BB3333" alt="Log4j Badge"> &nbsp;<br>
        Utilizes TestNG 7.4.0 for running tests. Incorporates Extent Reports 2.0 for detailed reporting. Integrates Log4j for comprehensive logging.
    </p>

   <h3>3. Multi-Platform Support</h3>
    <p>
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/Windows/10/00BFFF?icon=windows" alt="Windows Badge"> &nbsp;
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/macOS/Big%20Sur/0078D6?icon=apple" alt="macOS Badge"> &nbsp;
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/Appium/1.22.0/339933?icon=appium" alt="Appium Badge"> &nbsp;<br>
        Compatible with Windows, macOS, Appium for Android, and Appium for iOS. Supports both native mobile application testing and mobile browser testing.
    </p>

   <h3>4. Cross-Browser Testing</h3>
    <p>
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/BrowserStack/Supported/0096FF?icon=browserstack" alt="BrowserStack Badge"> &nbsp;<br>
        Enables cross-browser testing using BrowserStack for a wide range of browser and device combinations.
    </p>

   <h3>5. Comprehensive Testing Coverage</h3>
    <p>
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/Web%20Application%20Testing/Supported/FF6347" alt="Web Application Testing Badge"> &nbsp;
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/RESTful%20API%20Testing/Supported/FF6347" alt="RESTful API Testing Badge"> &nbsp;
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/Database%20Testing/Supported/FF6347" alt="Database Testing Badge"> &nbsp;
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/Accessibility%20Testing/Supported/FF6347" alt="Accessibility Testing Badge"> &nbsp;<br>
        Supports web application testing. Facilitates mobile native application testing. Allows mobile browser testing. Enables BrowserStack testing. Provides RESTful API automation testing. Supports all types of database testing. Includes accessibility testing.
    </p>

   <h3>6. SOLID Principles and Modular Framework</h3>
    <p>
        <img src="https://badgen.net/badge/SOLID%20Principles/Compliant/1F4E78" alt="SOLID Principles Badge"> &nbsp;<br>
        Designed using SOLID principles to ensure high cohesion and low coupling. Offers a modular framework for easy maintenance and scalability.
    </p>
    <p>
        This framework is a comprehensive package that supports web application testing, mobile native application testing, mobile browser testing, cross-browser testing, RESTful API automation testing, all types of database testing, and accessibility testing. It is built on the principles of SOLID design, ensuring a maintainable and scalable solution for your testing needs.
    </p>

## Advanced Topics
<img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Advanced%20Topics-CI%2FCD%20%26%20Parallel%20Execution-d33833?logo=jenkins" alt="Advanced Topics Badge"> &nbsp;

<p>
    Our framework delves into cutting-edge features that elevate your testing capabilities. In our <a href="docs/advanced_topic.md">Advanced Topics</a> guide, you'll discover how to seamlessly integrate with CI/CD pipelines to automate your testing process, utilize Selenium Grid for executing tests in parallel across multiple browsers and environments, and implement custom TestNG listeners to tailor test execution and reporting to your needs. These advanced techniques are designed to optimize test efficiency, enhance test coverage, and ensure your automation framework is robust and scalable.
</p>


## Execution Reports
<img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/ExecutionReport-Extent%20Report%20v2.41.2-2591ec?logo=data:image/svg+xml;base64,"alt="Extent Report Badge">

<p>Our framework generates detailed execution reports using Extent Reports. These reports provide comprehensive insights into test execution and outcomes, making it easier to analyze test results and improve your testing strategies.<p>

<ul style="margin-top: 0; padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: disc;">
           <li style="margin-bottom: 2px;">
        <strong>Location:</strong> All reports are stored within <a href="./Sprint-Execution-Reports/extent-reports" target="_blank">Open Sprint Execution Reports</a> in the project directory.
    </li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 2px;">
        <strong>Formats:</strong> Extent Reports are available in HTML format for thorough review.
    </li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 2px;">
        <strong>Access:</strong> HTML reports can be viewed by opening the files in any web browser.
    </li>
      </ul>
